<item>
            <title>[JDK-8324598] use mem_unit when working with sysinfo memory and swap related information</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8324598</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>According to the sysinfo manpage  ( &lt;a href=&quot;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/sysinfo.2.html&quot;&gt;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/sysinfo.2.html&lt;/a&gt; ) the memory and swap related  entries in the  struct sysinfo are  given as multiples of mem_unit bytes.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;In the above structure, sizes of the memory and swap fields are given as multiples of mem_unit bytes.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is considered in most parts of the OpenJDK codebase when sysinfo is used but not all; should be added where it is missing.</description>
